  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "Solidity `solc` compiler provides interesting information on the [NetSpec documentation](https://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/v0.7.4/natspec-format.html#documentation-output) of compiled contracts. `userdoc` and `devdoc` fields in the [`contractOutput`](https://github.com/nomiclabs/hardhat/blob/master/packages/hardhat-core/src/internal/artifacts.ts#L447) object could be easily included in the JSON build files, and be used, for example, to create a hardhat plugin to generate documentation similar to [solidity-docgen](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/solidity-docgen) of OpenZeppelin.",
